00:44:42.940 --> 00:44:45.530
that if you don't have
elongation by telomerase,

00:44:45.530 --> 00:44:48.380
the telomeres can be
elongated by recombination

00:44:48.380 --> 00:44:51.380
and this is harking back
to what was proposed

00:44:51.380 --> 00:44:53.163
about 10 years earlier.

00:44:54.060 --> 00:44:56.840
And that is the recombination telomeres.

00:44:56.840 --> 00:44:58.980
So the discovery of telomerase led

00:44:58.980 --> 00:45:00.330
to being able to ask the question

00:45:00.330 --> 00:45:03.280
about what are the
consequences of short telomeres

00:45:03.280 --> 00:45:07.320
and remarkably, recombination
is one of those consequences

00:45:07.320 --> 00:45:09.740
and this is something that again,

00:45:09.740 --> 00:45:13.940
the process doesn't
necessarily work linearly.

00:45:13.940 --> 00:45:17.193
Recombination was proposed
a number of years before.

00:45:18.260 --> 00:45:20.430
The cellular senescence

00:45:20.430 --> 00:45:22.530
is one of the consequence of telomeres.

00:45:22.530 --> 00:45:24.646
Initiation, the DNA damage response

00:45:24.646 --> 00:45:28.613
and cell death was another consequence.

00:45:29.810 --> 00:45:34.810
So the overall synthesis of this

00:45:35.010 --> 00:45:38.210
is that defining the molecular components

00:45:38.210 --> 00:45:40.070
together with understanding
the consequences

00:45:40.070 --> 00:45:42.640
of short telomeres allowed the discovery

00:45:42.640 --> 00:45:44.840
of human disease mechanism.

00:45:44.840 --> 00:45:48.910
So many of these components
that we've been building up

00:45:48.910 --> 00:45:52.770
over the years then led
to the understanding

00:45:52.770 --> 00:45:56.600
of the human genetic disease
dyskeratosis congenita.

00:45:56.600 --> 00:45:58.520
So understanding the telomeres RNA

00:45:58.520 --> 00:46:01.180
and understanding the
consequences of short telomeres

00:46:01.180 --> 00:46:05.110
led to knowing that this disease

00:46:05.110 --> 00:46:08.490
is actually a disease of short telomeres

00:46:08.490 --> 00:46:11.440
which then several years later made clear

00:46:11.440 --> 00:46:15.230
that there are really a
collection of different effects

00:46:15.230 --> 00:46:20.180
of short telomeres often
called the telomere syndrome.

00:46:20.180 --> 00:46:22.850
Understanding these consequences puts new

00:46:22.850 --> 00:46:25.670
understanding about
telomere length regulation

00:46:25.670 --> 00:46:30.530
and these experiments are
really still the focus

00:46:30.530 --> 00:46:32.720
of many different laboratories today.

00:46:32.720 --> 00:46:36.580
So as I was concluding yesterday,

00:46:36.580 --> 00:46:39.557
discovery is not a linear process

00:46:39.557 --> 00:46:43.060
and new discoveries sometimes
come from unlikely places.

00:46:43.060 --> 00:46:45.763
Tetrahymena and Oxytricha.

00:46:47.210 --> 00:46:52.170
