00:57:48.970 --> 00:57:50.800
and there has also been on the other side

00:57:50.800 --> 00:57:53.750
some interest in looking
at telomerase inhibitors

00:57:53.750 --> 00:57:55.780
as approaches to cancer.

00:57:55.780 --> 00:57:57.600
But now that we know a little bit more

00:57:57.600 --> 00:58:00.900
about the normal consequences
of having less telomerase,

00:58:00.900 --> 00:58:02.700
we need to just step back
and think a little bit

00:58:02.700 --> 00:58:06.530
about how long you would
want to inhibit telomerase

00:58:06.530 --> 00:58:08.430
before you may have other effects.

00:58:08.430 --> 00:58:11.490
So one needs to have a little
bit more of a nuanced approach

00:58:11.490 --> 00:58:13.770
but these are definitely areas

00:58:13.770 --> 00:58:16.999
that people are actively
trying to understand

00:58:16.999 --> 00:58:20.060
as we understand the disease,

00:58:20.060 --> 00:58:21.900
understanding treatments for the disease.

00:58:21.900 --> 00:58:25.820
My colleagues at Hopkins
see patients every day

00:58:25.820 --> 00:58:27.210
that are dying from these diseases

00:58:27.210 --> 00:58:29.580
and there's no treatment
so we were very interested

00:58:29.580 --> 00:58:31.230
in pursuing that.

00:58:31.230 --> 00:58:32.193
Thank you.

